.TH "pci_request_regions_exclusive" 9 "pci_request_regions_exclusive" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_request_regions_exclusive \- Reserve PCI I/O and memory resources
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_request_regions_exclusive
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ","
.BI "const char *res_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device whose resources are to be reserved
.IP "res_name" 12
Name to be associated with resource.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Mark all PCI regions associated with PCI device \fIpdev\fP as being reserved
by owner \fIres_name\fP.  Do not access any address inside the PCI regions
unless this call returns successfully.

\fBpci_request_regions_exclusive\fP will mark the region so that /dev/mem
and the sysfs MMIO access will not be allowed.

Returns 0 on success, or EBUSY on error.  A warning message is also
printed on failure.
